benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: PUT /1.0/kb/accounts/{accountId}/customFields - Modify custom fields to account

covered: PUT method: Valid Request scenarios (TC01, TC02, TC03, TC04, TC05) including large payload (TC04) and empty array edge case (TC15)
Error handling and validation (TC06, TC07, TC08, TC09, TC10, TC11)
Server availability and dependency failures (TC13, TC14, TC22)
Concurrency and performance (TC25, TC26, TC27, TC28, TC29)
Edge and integration scenarios (TC16, TC17, TC18, TC19, TC23, TC24, TC27, TC28, TC29)
gaps: Partial update behavior: No explicit test covering rejection or validation of partial updates when only some fields are provided (the tests mostly assume full replacement).
Caching behavior and ETag/Cache-Control headers are not covered for PUT responses.
Rate limiting/throttling tests are not present for PUT /customFields.
Pagination is not applicable to PUT, but no guidance on testing related to batch processing or multiple accounts in a single call is provided beyond TC25.
recommendations: Add a dedicated Partial Update test to verify that partial payloads are rejected if not allowed (or to confirm full-replace semantics).
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag/Cache-Control) for PUT responses where applicable.
Introduce rate limiting/throttling tests for spike load scenarios on PUT /customFields.
Consider explicit tests for batch/atomicity behavior if the API supports transactional updates across multiple accounts in a single operation.
